documentation.author: CERNER
documentation.purpose: Create values for clinical events based documentation regarding reasons why Antithrombotic Therapy was not given.
documentation.explanation: STK 5 is a Core Measure for stroke patient receiving antithrombotic therapy by end of hospital day 2.
documentation.query: 8/24/11 - Removed action templates A2 and A3 and logic templates L50 - 54. This removed updating the goal. Changed action 1 to send back through Discern Expert. Also added age template to evaluate for greater than 18 years of age. Versioned DTA Reg STK Rea Antithrombotic NtGvn Day2 vA to vB. 9/26/11 - added evoke on Quality measures Dashboard initiated 10/4/11 - changed evoke on Quality measures dashboard initiated to look at both Ordered and Completed statuses 10/5/11 - adding in allergy meds, removed action to exclude patient from measure, added creating dta Reg STK Antithrombotic by End Day 2 with value of No
documentation.impact:
The following needs to be addressed at each client site:
All scripts need to be present in any environment this rule is to run in
All Build Param templates require PARAMVALUE to be reinstantiated
All Problem and Diagnosis templates need to be reinstantiated
ALL ACTIONS
VALUE1 needs to be reinstantiated

PowerForm STK 5 Antithrombotic Therapy
Reference B

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ALLERGY_E
templateDefinitions.definition: Allergy action is ACTION_TYPE and allergy ALLERGY_QUAL OPT_ALLERGY for OPT_CATEGORY category with reaction OPT_REACTION_QUAL OPT_REACTION and OPT_REACTION_TYPE, OPT_REACTION_STATUS, OPT_SEVERITY, OPT_INFO_SOURCE, OPT_CANCEL_REASON. Optionally narrow allergy matching by limiting cross-mapping to OPT_CROSS_VOCABS vocabularies OPT_PERSON_ACTIVITY concepts on patient’s profile and/or OPT_VOCAB_HIERARCHY hierarchy or ignoring concepts altogether OPT_IGNORE_CONCEPTS.

templateDefinitions.definition: An allergy exists that ALLERGY_QUAL OPT_ALLERGY for OPT_CATEGORY category with reaction OPT_REACTION_QUAL OPT_REACTION and OPT_REACTION_TYPE, OPT_REACTION_STATUS, OPT_SEVERITY, OPT_INFO_SOURCE, OPT_CANCEL_REASON. Optionally narrow allergy matching by limiting cross-mapping to OPT_CROSS_VOCABS vocabularies OPT_PERSON_ACTIVITY concepts on patient’s profile and/or OPT_VOCAB_HIERARCHY hierarchy or ignoring concepts altogether OPT_IGNORE_CONCEPTS. templateDefinitions.name: EKS_BUILD_PARAM_L
templateDefinitions.definition: ACTION a dynamic parameter named PARAMNAME with a value of PARAMVALUE. And OPT_SUBSTITUTION resolve substitution value.
templateDefinitions.description: Create or add to a dynamic parameter to be used by subsequent templates.

statements.statement:
select action = if (d.seq = 1) "Create" elseif (d.seq = 2) "Append To" ENDIF, _hidden = if (d.seq = 1) "1" elseif (d.seq = 2) "2" ENDIF
FROM (DUMMYT D WITH SEQ = VALUE(2))
select param_value ="Double click in lower box to enter a freetext value, or right click and paste values that have been copied", _hidden = " " from (dummyt d with seq = 1)

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_PROBLEMS_FIND_L
templateDefinitions.definition: OPT_PROBLEMS exist with OPT_QUALIFIER, OPT_CONFIRMATION, OPT_CLASSIFICATION, OPT_LIFE_CYCLE_STATUS, OPT_SEVERITY_CLASS, OPT_SEVERITY, OPT_COURSE for person LINK. Optionally narrow problem matching by limiting cross-mapping to OPT_CROSS_VOCABS vocabularies OPT_PERSON_ACTIVITY concepts on patient’s profile and/or OPT_VOCAB_HIERARCHY hierarchy or ignoring concepts altogether OPT_IGNORE_CONCEPTS. templateDefinitions.definition: Create a STATUS, OPT_NORMALCY, EVENT_NAME result of VALUE1 OPT_UNITS_OF_MEASURE on the same encounter as LINK with OPT_COMMENT_TYPE of OPT_COMMENT and RESEND send this event back through Discern Expert.
